alert.note: Alert for Carver; Dakota; Hennepin; Scott (Minnesota) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued May 22 at 11:16PM CDT until May 27 at 7:00PM CDT by NWS Minneapolis
info.description: ...The Flood Warning is extended for the following rivers in Minnesota... Minnesota River near Jordan affecting Sibley, Scott and Carver Counties. ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Minnesota... Minnesota River at Savage affecting Hennepin, Dakota, Scott and Carver Counties. ...The Flood Warning is cancelled for the following rivers in Minnesota and Wisconsin... Minnesota River at Henderson MN19 affecting Sibley, Scott and Le Sueur Counties. Mississippi River near Hastings L/D 2 (COE) affecting Dakota, Pierce, Goodhue and Washington Counties. Mississippi River at St. Paul affecting Dakota, Washington and Ramsey Counties. .Rivers have crested and will continue to fall this week. ...FLOOD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL SATURDAY EVENING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Minnesota River at Savage. * WHEN...Until Saturday evening. * IMPACTS...At 705.0 feet, Flood waters begin to impact the park road at Fort Snelling State Park. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 1100 PM CDT Monday, the stage was 706.5 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 1100 PM CDT Monday was 706.9 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to fall below flood stage early Saturday morning and continue falling to 699.5 feet Monday evening. - Flood stage is 702.0 feet. &&
info.instruction: Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
